commit.message:
gray: remove an sbcl deadlock workaround.

finish-output doesn't do anything now if there's an auto-flush thread.

sbcl/restart-frame: restart the generic function of a method.

Calling the same method function is rarely useful.

Fixes #819
sbcl, thread-status: show if it's waiting on a mutex.

Buffer FINISH-OUTPUT calls.

It'll be flushed pretty quickly by the auto-flush thread. Otherwise
continuous output becomes really slow.
Drop incomplete compatibility support for Emacs <24.3

Signal user-errors instead of errors for user facing interactive functions

Using `error` for signaling errors cause entry to the Emacs debugger
if it is enabled.
For interactive user facing functions it is better to use `user-error`
instead, that signals an incorrect manipulation by the user, not an
actual problem.

Docs of `user-error`:

"This is like error except that a user error (or "pilot error") comes
from an incorrect manipulation by the user, not from an actual problem.
In contrast with other errors, user errors normally do not cause
entry to the debugger, even when debug-on-error is non-nil."

slime-fuzzy: better restoration of window configuration.

Just use quit-window.

Fix buttons in slime-trace-dialog

This small fix is needed for buttons to work in slime-trace-dialog.

Partially revert "Fix .gitignore for ELPA and remove cl-lib"

This reverts some of the changes made in
6e0d67b9b7ae0fc31902609ab7525826b292c384.
* slime.el: Add autoload cookies for entry points
Pass a code, not a character, to %utf8-encode
